      "content": "hey i'm working on this embedded c++ project for an automotive sensor module and we're seeing a slow memory leak. the heap just gradually drains over like 4-5 hours of runtime until it crashes. i dont see any obvious new/delete mismatches in the main loop. can u give me a systematic way to track down where the leak is coming from? \n\nhere is the snippet for the logging buffer:\n\nvoid log_event(const char* msg) {\n    char* buffer = new char[256];\n    strncpy(buffer, msg, 255);\n    buffer[255] = '\\0';\n    event_queue.push(buffer);\n}\n\nlooks okay at first glance but it's definitely eating RAM.",
